of the actual development of the website.

00:28:02.613 --> 00:28:07.133
We started building out in a rough state
some of these key pages

00:28:07.188 --> 00:28:10.845
and actually just setting up
the bones of the WordPress website.

00:28:11.641 --> 00:28:12.641
Now, a quick aside

00:28:12.719 --> 00:28:14.826
on how we developed
the WordPress website,

00:28:15.170 --> 00:28:16.420
including this prototype,

00:28:16.965 --> 00:28:20.815
we had to make a decision on the tools
that we were going to use in WordPress.

00:28:20.904 --> 00:28:24.710
One of the decisions we made early on
was to use the Divi theme,

00:28:24.773 --> 00:28:26.811
which comes with a visual builder,

00:28:27.467 --> 00:28:31.343
and to amend
some of Divi's shortcomings

00:28:31.426 --> 00:28:33.395
when it comes to accessibility through

00:28:33.482 --> 00:28:36.136
there's a special plugin
called Divi Accessibility.

00:28:36.627 --> 00:28:38.617
We wrote some custom JavaScript too

00:28:38.696 --> 00:28:43.220
to amend some of the downsides
of some of the Divi content.

00:28:44.063 --> 00:28:47.213
You might be wondering,
well, why not just use WordPress blocks?

00:28:47.600 --> 00:28:50.436
The WordPress accessibility team has
been developing

00:28:50.515 --> 00:28:52.636
and putting a lot of effort
into the block editor

00:28:52.731 --> 00:28:55.409
and full site editing
and block theming,

00:28:55.464 --> 00:28:57.664
and it's really moving
in a great direction.

00:28:57.746 --> 00:28:59.518
We're huge fans of that effort.

00:28:59.920 --> 00:29:01.741
We do lots of websites that way.

00:29:02.384 --> 00:29:04.013
There were a few considerations

00:29:04.365 --> 00:29:10.106
when we decided to use Divi
to create the visual design of the site.

00:29:10.709 --> 00:29:11.709
One was that

00:29:11.887 --> 00:29:15.597
Braille Institute has
a very small content editing team in-house

00:29:15.636 --> 00:29:19.262
that they could train and coordinate
when using Divi.

00:29:20.012 --> 00:29:24.232
Also, none of those people at the time
had a visual disability,

00:29:24.356 --> 00:29:27.716
so nobody needed
the editor of the web content

00:29:27.826 --> 00:29:29.412
to be fully accessible.

00:29:29.882 --> 00:29:33.823
We could depend on that
as a constraint.

00:29:34.398 --> 00:29:35.398
Also,

00:29:36.067 --> 00:29:38.217
this would allow Braille Institute
to create

00:29:38.334 --> 00:29:42.278
new layouts and new design patterns
for the website over time

00:29:42.382 --> 00:29:46.459
without having to invest effort
in development and writing more code.

00:29:46.542 --> 00:29:51.299
They could create
layouts, pages, design patterns

00:29:52.123 --> 00:29:54.268
with ease using the visual builder.

00:29:54.649 --> 00:29:59.179
Finally, Braille Institute has
a WordPress developer in-house on staff

00:29:59.274 --> 00:30:00.274
who knows Divi

00:30:00.395 --> 00:30:03.840
and can maintain the accessibility
of the website that we created.

00:30:04.070 --> 00:30:07.511
For all of those reasons,
it made sense to use Divi as the theme.

00:30:07.644 --> 00:30:09.700
We also used
a couple of other plugins

00:30:10.169 --> 00:30:12.769
to supplement that
for the front end of the website.

00:30:13.150 --> 00:30:17.103
Gravity Forms is well known
for having highly accessible forms.

00:30:17.516 --> 00:30:20.098
We used that.
We styled them using Divi.

00:30:20.427 --> 00:30:24.488
G Translate provides
the language translation for the website.

00:30:24.707 --> 00:30:27.557
It's available
in about a half dozen different languages.

00:30:28.477 --> 00:30:29.477
It works well

00:30:29.533 --> 00:30:33.174
in that it changes the lang
attribute on the HTML tag

00:30:33.311 --> 00:30:37.876
to the actual language
that the page is translated into,

00:30:37.941 --> 00:30:40.291
so that a screen reader can hear
all of the text

00:30:40.343 --> 00:30:42.433
pronounced properly
in that language.

00:30:44.747 --> 00:30:46.075
For the usability testing,

00:30:46.136 --> 00:30:49.806
we did in-person moderated testing
for most of the users.

00:30:49.890 --> 00:30:52.514
There were 15 users in three groups.

00:30:52.705 --> 00:30:57.065
A low vision set of users of five,
five blind users,

00:30:57.159 --> 00:30:58.915
and then five sighted users.

00:30:59.510 --> 00:31:02.272
They used
a variety of assistive technologies.

00:31:02.533 --> 00:31:05.965
We had JAWS available, NVDA,
both screen readers,

00:31:06.340 --> 00:31:09.172
as well as ZoomText
for screen magnification.

00:31:10.391 --> 00:31:14.815
We went on site
in Braille Institute's Los Angeles center.

00:31:15.635 --> 00:31:16.929
We had a room set up

00:31:17.031 --> 00:31:20.775
with large monitors
and a large-format keyboard,

00:31:20.842 --> 00:31:22.773
as well as a mouse available.

00:31:24.106 --> 00:31:27.755
In addition to those software solutions
that I mentioned a minute ago.

00:31:28.185 --> 00:31:31.009
We sat alongside the user
and had them click through

00:31:31.092 --> 00:31:34.809
and try to complete
a series of tasks on the prototype.

00:31:34.903 --> 00:31:38.567
We recorded and observed
what they were doing

00:31:38.990 --> 00:31:43.424
so that we could collate our findings
and make changes to the design.

00:31:43.925 --> 00:31:45.053
What we learned,

00:31:45.419 --> 00:31:48.747
there's a few things
that we altered in the design

00:31:49.193 --> 00:31:50.993
which you will see on the live site.

00:31:51.683 --> 00:31:52.683
The first thing is

00:31:52.741 --> 00:31:55.277
that the offering cards
that we had originally

00:31:55.980 --> 00:32:02.060
had this eyebrow text above at the top
in that green bar in the offering card.

00:32:02.620 --> 00:32:06.517
It used to say things
like new, in-person, online,

00:32:06.947 --> 00:32:10.323
in the green bar
above the heading for the card.

00:32:11.503 --> 00:32:14.854
It was all grouped together
using the black lines

00:32:14.911 --> 00:32:18.894
to associate that content together
as one offering.

00:32:19.510 --> 00:32:22.049
The difficulty with that is that,

00:32:22.513 --> 00:32:27.319
without the styles available here,
if you're just listening to the webpage,

00:32:27.993 --> 00:32:32.142
you might hear a series of things
that are more like raw content.

00:32:33.799 --> 00:32:35.649
This is what the page would look like

00:32:35.743 --> 00:32:38.200
without any style sheet
associated with it.

00:32:38.286 --> 00:32:41.690
You can see
that the new in-person and online text

00:32:42.191 --> 00:32:45.210
doesn't necessarily look associated
with what's below it.

00:32:45.404 --> 00:32:47.904
It could look just
as associated with what's above.

00:32:48.294 --> 00:32:51.390
That association of the black line
through the style sheet,

00:32:51.984 --> 00:32:54.344
when it's not available for some users

00:32:54.428 --> 00:32:56.278
who are, again, listening to the page

00:32:56.340 --> 00:33:00.074
or are low vision
and can't see the design as well,

00:33:00.742 --> 00:33:01.997
made it more difficult.

00:33:02.726 --> 00:33:06.469
The change that we made was
to move the eyebrow text below the heading

00:33:06.835 --> 00:33:08.885
and move the heading
up into the green bar

00:33:08.974 --> 00:33:11.428
so that the heading, which is the title,

00:33:12.421 --> 00:33:15.784
precedes all of the content
that it's the title for.

00:33:15.929 --> 00:33:17.279
That made a big difference.

00:33:18.388 --> 00:33:19.838
Another thing we did is that,

00:33:20.177 --> 00:33:22.112
the main menu panel has

00:33:22.191 --> 00:33:25.088
a series of toggle buttons
for each menu item

00:33:25.159 --> 00:33:27.953
that
expands the second-level navigation.

00:33:28.298 --> 00:33:31.655
Those were off to the right side
within the menu panel.

00:33:32.447 --> 00:33:33.497
We were finding users

00:33:33.555 --> 00:33:36.362
weren't always discovering those arrows
off to the right,

00:33:36.464 --> 00:33:39.574
and they were missing
that important action for navigating.

00:33:39.989 --> 00:33:42.960
What we did was
we moved the arrows back to the left side,

00:33:43.810 --> 00:33:48.194
to the left of the menu link
that it refers to.

00:33:48.646 --> 00:33:50.196
The order is still going to be,

00:33:50.297 --> 00:33:52.410
when you're encountering the page
from top to bottom,

00:33:52.473 --> 00:33:56.060
the main menu parent link
followed by the arrow.

00:33:56.174 --> 00:34:00.152
It will go to the link first
and then to the left, to the arrow,

00:34:00.230 --> 00:34:02.240
so that that hierarchy is still clear.

00:34:02.779 --> 00:34:06.629
This made a big difference for users
traveling down the left side of the page.

00:34:07.230 --> 00:34:10.211
Also,
icons were present in the design.

00:34:10.595 --> 00:34:13.524
We were finding that,
the way these were implemented,

00:34:13.845 --> 00:34:16.371
it would create a pause
in a screen reader.

00:34:16.675 --> 00:34:19.570
Somebody would advance
to the next element on the page

00:34:19.680 --> 00:34:20.680
and hear nothing.

00:34:21.655 --> 00:34:25.883
That minor stumble
was tripping up a lot of people,

00:34:26.032 --> 00:34:27.182
and they were confused.

00:34:27.967 --> 00:34:30.167
We realized
we don't really need these icons.

00:34:30.274 --> 00:34:32.955
We have text labels
associated with them already.

00:34:33.050 --> 00:34:36.917
We just got rid of the icons fonts,
and that removed that hurdle.

00:34:38.892 --> 00:34:40.572
We added more descriptive text.

00:34:40.967 --> 00:34:44.295
The main call to action on the homepage
used to say, "Get Started,"

00:34:44.547 --> 00:34:45.947
which is a little ambiguous.

00:34:46.040 --> 00:34:48.362
What will I get if I click get started?

00:34:48.998 --> 00:34:49.998
